title.narrative: Second State Statistical System Development Project

description.narrative: The main objective of the project to assist the government of the Russian Federation to produce reliable, timely and accurate economic, financial, socio-demographic and other data for policy formulation and decision making in line with international good practiceand frameworks.

title.narrative: Number of new surveys and/or modules of data collection
Availability of data collected through remote/distanced methods

target.value: Number of abolished statistical forms and questionnaires exceeds the number of newly introduced ones.

actual.value: Revision of currently used questionnaires took place. The balance of abolished statistical forms and newly introduced is positive.

title.narrative: Share of statistical information provided by Rosstat to the users according to established time schedule
Computer equipment of Rosstat staff (MODERN computer equipment)
Number of statistical tasks resolved on a new technological basis and forwarded to the United Foundation of algorithms and programs

actual.value: All statistical tasks are being resolved on a new technological basis since 2011. Thus no longer active.

title.narrative: Total number of classifications used throughout the SSS that are compatible with the equivalent international classifications
Regular analysis of users' satisfaction (Index of users' trust to official statistical data)

target.value: 1.04 and sustained annual regularity or once in two years.

title.narrative: Number of Rosstat website visits per annum (thousands)

target.value: Positive dynamics of Rosstat web site visits throughout the project up to 1000K.

title.narrative: Number of MDG indicators produced by the SSS
Number of sample surveys in different economic and social fields that are conducted on a census basis
Dynamics of Rosstat staff training (number of trained staff) (persons)

target.value: The number of employees of Rosstat who trained under public order including the STASYS-2.

title.narrative: Mastering of international standards (filling out the statistical questionnaires of International Organizations with harmonized indicators)

actual.value: End target value reached in 2010 and maintained until 2014. Since then it has been replaced by indicator "Application ofinternationally accepted statistical methodologies and standards (filling out questionnaires of international organizations listedin the Federal Statistical Action Plan and official OECD questionnaires), %" due to changes in the set of internationalquestionnaires used for filling in and submission.
Statistical Council has been established and functioning since 2012.

title.narrative: Availability of data on skilled labor, demand for skilled labor

actual.value: Yes. Survey is conducted every two years. The next one is scheduled for 2020.

title.narrative: Compliance with the ICLS household income and expenditure methodology
Availability of HBS and LFS microdata bases for users in open access

baseline.value: Pilot (open access to sample HBS microdata for 2003 and 2004)

target.value: The HBS microdata sets are in public access. The microdata on living conditions of populations and the LFS microdata sets are alsoin public access on Rosstat website.

title.narrative: Dynamics of state budget expenditures for training purposes (thousand rubles)

baseline.value: Unstable dynamics of budget allocations for training purposes

target.value: Prevailing of state budget financing of Rosstat training during the entire project period

title.narrative: Data quality assessment for National Accounts Statistics (NAS) (as per DQAF for National Accounts Statistics as detailed in the IMF2012 Guidelines)

baseline.value: 2007 - no self-assessments done. First time in 2010 -1.

title.narrative: Application of internationally accepted statistical methodologies and standards (questionnaires of international organizations listed in Federal Statistical Action Plan and official OECD questionnaire
Number of systemic statistical tasks moved to centralized primary statistical data processing
Number of methodological guidelines prepared for implementation for compiling satellite accounts in the social sphere recommended by OECD

Degree of implementation of 2008 SNA into Russian statistical practices (% of works fulfilled in accordance with "Action Plan to implement OECD recommendations for developing the SNA in Russian Federa
Regional Statistical Offices employees dealing with receiving and processing primary statistical data (as % of 2015)
Share of official statistical reporting forms that could be submitted to NSO electronically (as % of 2015)
Number of statistical indicators based on electronic economic description as percent of the total number of statistical indicators assessed by Rosstat
Number of SDG indicators assessed by official statistical accounting bodies based on international methodology and introduced into Federal Statistical Action Plan
Availability of national set of indicators for SDG monitoring in the Russian Federation

target.value: A set of national SDG indicators is defined, and data are available.

actual.value: In 2018 – review and clarification of indicators for national set. In 2019 – final draft of national set and submission of thisdraft to the working group for sustainable development of Presidential Administration and the Government of Russia.
